                <note rend="inline" type="source">814.01/35b: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Missions in Costa Rica, El Salvador, Honduras,
                            and Nicaragua</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-01-06T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 6, 1931—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The American Minister in Guatemala has been instructed to extend the recognition
                    of the Government of the United States to the Government of Señor Andrade on the
                    afternoon of January 8, the call for elections having been issued. Inform the
                    Government to which you are accredited immediately of the proposed action of the
                    Government of the United States. The Minister in Guatemala has also been
                    instructed to inform his Central American colleagues of the action he is
                    taking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
